#7 LAKERS at #2 SUNS | FULL GAME HIGHLIGHTS | May 25, 2021

Led by Anthony Davisâ€™ 34 PTS, 10 REB and 7 AST, the No. 7 seed Los Angeles Lakers defeated the No. 2 seed Phoenix Suns, 109-102, in Game 2. Additionally for the Lakers, LeBron James recorded 23 PTS, 4 REB and 9 AST in the victory, while Devin Booker tallied a team-high 31 PTS for the Suns in the losing effort. This best-of-seven series is now tied, 1-1.
